# Netlify redirect rules.
#
# Default behavior on this site is SPA fallback (unknown paths -> index.html).
# That's the right call for client-routed pages, but it would eat the
# generated LLM-readable assets. The rules below force exact-match (200)
# for those files before the SPA fallback can grab them.
#
# Vike's prerender + Netlify's static-asset detection should already do
# this, but explicit > implicit.

# LLM-readable docs — exact-match before the SPA fallback can grab them.
/*.md            /:splat              200!
/llms.txt        /llms.txt            200!
/llms-full.txt   /llms-full.txt       200!
